'''PhÃ¹ng Kháº¯c Khoan''' (1528&ndash;1613), known as Trang Bung, was a noted 16th-century [[Vietnamese people|Vietnamese]] [[Military strategy|military strategist]], [[politician]], [[diplomat]] and poet during the [[Later LÃª dynasty warlord period]].
Phung Khac Khoan headed the diplomatic corps to China during the [[Ming Dynasty|Ming]], during which he took part in a notable summit colloquy, conducted in writing, with the [[Korea]]n historian [[Yi Su-gwang]] in 1597.
